data.title: Thelonious Monk transcriptions: Ruby My Dear, Round Midnight, Honeysuckle Rose, April in Paris
data.meta_description: Transcriptions of Thelonious Monk's jazz piano solos Ruby My Dear, Round Midnight, Honeysuckle Rose, April in Paris
data.text:
Birth name: Thelious Monk Jr.

Born: October 10, 1917, Rocky Mount, North Carolina, U.S.

Died: February 17, 1982 (aged 64), Englewood, New Jersey, U.S.

Thelonious Sphere Monk was an American jazz pianist and composer. He had a unique improvisational style and made numerous contributions to the standard jazz repertoire, including "'Round Midnight", "Blue Monk", "Straight, No Chaser", "Ruby, My Dear", "In Walked Bud", and "Well, You Needn't". Monk is the second-most-recorded jazz composer after Duke Ellington.
